com.graphql_java_generator.plugin.language

Interface Field

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FieldImpl

    public interface Field
    This interface describes one field of one objet type (or interface...). It aims to be simple enough, so that the Velocity template can easily generated ths fields from it.
    For instance: 
     name: String!
    is a Field of name 'name', type 'String', and is mandatory. or 
     appearsIn: [Episode!]!
    is a Field of name 'appearsIn', type 'Episode', is a list, is mandatory and its items are mandatory.
    Author:
    EtienneSF

      • getGraphQLTypeName

        String getGraphQLTypeName()
        The type of this field, as defined in the GraphQL schema. This type is either the type of the field (if it's not a list), or the type of the items in the list (if it's a list)

      • isId

        boolean isId()
        Indicates whether this field is an id or not. It's used in PluginMode#SERVER mode to add the javax.persistence annotations for the id fields. Default value is false. This field is set to true for GraphQL fields which are of 'ID' type.

      • getInputParameters

        boolean isMandatory()
